<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 6:07PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact southeastern Cascade County
through 630 PM MDT...
At 604 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strengthening
thunderstorm located west of Monarch and Neihart, moving east at 25
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Neihart and Monarch.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors or in campgrounds, consider seeking shelter inside a
building.</instruction>
